news.title: Godrej Properties acquires additional one acre land parcel in Bengaluru
news.para: The land has a developable potential of approximately 1.40 lakh sq ft saleable area. Godrej Properties plans to develop premium residential apartments on the land parcel.

news.title: Talks on to cut property tax fines in Bengaluru: Karnataka deputy CM
news.para: Shivakumar was speaking at the grievance-redressal programme ‘Government at your Doorstep’ in Gandhinagar. He said there were a lot of appeals seeking reduction in property tax and penalties for 30x40 sites and sheds.

news.title: Mumbai: Lookout notice against Supreme Constructions, partners for duping flat buyers
news.para: Two separate FIRs were registered on Tuesday at Chembur and Taloja police stations against Tekchandani, his wife, Arun Makhija, Miza Hassan Ibrahim and other directors of Supreme Constructions.

news.title: Noida: 56% stamp revenue target met, government pins hope on rehabilitation deal for registries
news.para: A revenue target of Rs 4,728 crore was set for the district in 2023-24. By December, the department had collected Rs 2,662 crore, which is 56 of the target. The department has registered 10,659 flats against 11,447 through the previous financial year.

news.title: Palava City annual revenue may top Rs 8,000 crore in a few years: Lodha
news.para: The development at Palava City started in 2010, with phase 1 covering 300 acres that was sold out and delivered to nearly 20,000 families in 4-5 years.

news.title: Delhi court grants 30-day interim bail to Supertech's chairman
news.para: Additional Sessions Judge Devender Kumar Jangala granted relief to the accused on a personal bond of Rs 1 lakh and two sureties of like amount.

news.title: Sweden's Oscar Properties sells real estate at discount to keep creditors at bay
news.para: "We would have liked to have continued to own these properties, but our senior bank DNB wanted to have its loans repaid," CEO Carl Janglin said in a statement on Monday.

news.title: Signa Prime Selection can fund operations, administrator says
news.para: Signa is the biggest casualty to date of Europe's property crisis. Its holding group at the centre of a complex constellation of around 1,000 companies filed for insolvency in November.

news.title: Country Garden appoints KPMG adviser for offshore debt restructuring
news.para: Country Garden, China's biggest private property developer, is among a long list of developers facing a cash crunch since being hit by a debt crisis in mid-2021.

news.title: BIS comes out with model building regulation for seamless adoption across nation
news.para: The model building regulation, Standardized Development and Building Regulations 2023, has been prepared after studying the provisions of the National Building Code (NBC) 2016 and existing national and global building regulations.

news.title: Scheme to divorcees, single women for constructing house to start soon: Himachal Pradesh CM
news.para: They include women who have been abandoned by their husbands or whose husbands are missing and single women who are orphans or those who do not have anybody to look after them.

news.title: Kerala: ED attaches assets worth over Rs 30 crore of Heera Construction Company
news.para: ​​A total of 62 immovable properties belonging to Heera Construction Company, its managing director Abdul Rasheed, his trust Heera Educational and Charitable Trust and sister company Heera Summer Holiday Homes have been attached under the provisions of the PMLA, the central agency said in a statement.

news.title: Ban lifted on sale of land in 34 villages of Indore district
news.para: According to senior registrar Deepak Kumar Sharma, the ban was imposed on sale and purchase of land in 34 villages of Hatod, Sanwer and Depalpur tehsil on November 24 last year as the district administration has instructed the concerned SDM to start land acquisition for construction of Western or Greater Indore Ring Road.

news.title: PM releases first instalment of benefits to one lakh people under tribal welfare scheme
news.para: ​Releasing the first instalment of Rs 540 crore to one lakh beneficiaries of a rural housing scheme under the Pradhan Mantri Janjati Adivasi Nyaya Maha Abhiyan (PM-JANMAN) via video conferencing, he said the 10 years of his government have been dedicated to the poor.

news.title: China: Logan Group's liquidation lawsuit adjourned on potential new petitioner
news.para: The latest development came after the Shenzhen developer said on Friday it had signed an agreement with a key bondholder group on the terms of restructuring its $6.6 billion in offshore debt.

news.title: Delhi: LG gives nod to notify 147 acres of land in Rani Khera for industrial development
news.para: The land was transferred to the Delhi State Industrial and Infrastructure Development Corporation (DSIIDC) from the Delhi Development Authority (DDA) in 2007.

news.title: Thane builder sentenced till 'rising of court' in cheque bounce case, fined Rs 41.44 lakh
news.para: Judicial Magistrate First Class, Thane, Harish Pardeshi, convicted Anil Thakurdas Kursija under section 138 of the Negotiable Instruments Act, 1881. He will have to face imprisonment for two more months if he fails to pay the fine in a month.

news.title: Plots unused for a decade, Noida authority cancels 30 allotments
news.para: According to Noida officials, completion and functional certificates were not obtained by 107 IT/ITES firms that were allotted plots after December 2022. In a recent survey, 78 of them were found to be in different stages of construction, while no construction was carried out on 29 plots.

news.title: Can't relax aviation safety norms for Mhada building: Bombay HC
news.para: ​"No relaxation of civil aviation safety norms can be granted only because the project proponent is a public authority. Aviation safety has nothing at all to do with the identity of the developer," said the HC in its January 10 order.
